The UN-sponsored climate conference -- characterized so far by disorganized assignments and mutual recriminations -- returned to the limelight on Friday, due to the release of a document outlining ambitious greenhouse gas reductions over the next 40 years, with industrialized nations shouldering most of the burden, in the coming days.
