Distribution (disambiguation)
This apparent paradox can be explained by the complex procedure for the distribution of money applied by UEFA.
For this year, the organization chaired by Michel Platini plans to earn 1,090 million thanks to the Champions League.
Of this sum, UEFA will devote €413.1 million to fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs that participated in the classification matches (among which Atlético de Madrid) received €2.1 million.
In addition, those who managed to participate received 3.8 million just to be there, in addition to 550 00 euros for each game played.
There is also a bonus in case of victory (800,000 euros) and equality (400,000 for each team). Those who arrive in the round of 16 receive three million each, the eight teams who arrive in the quarter-final receive 3.3 million.
The last four teams will each receive $4 million.
And the champion will win 9 million, against the 5.2 received by the other finalist.
Thus, under fixed payments, a club will earn at least 7.1 million, and a maximum of 31.2 million.
On the other hand, Bar<0xC3><0xA7>a pocketed 2.5 million for winning the European Super Cup in August.
But in addition, there are variable payments, to which 337.8 million are devoted.
This money is distributed according to the proportional value of each television market.
The Spanish market is one of the most important, and has four dedicated seats.
The champion of the previous year pocketed 40% of the money allocated, 30% for the second, 20% for the third and 10% for the fourth.
The other part will be paid according to the number of games played during the current year's edition.
